syncfix3-fix2: Don't mark ERROR on timeout if chain is 100% synced

When sync activity/liveness/progress timeout fires, check if the chain
is actually fully synced (local atoms >= network atoms) before marking
CHAIN_SYNC_STATE_ERROR. If synced, mark CHAIN_SYNC_STATE_SYNCED instead.
Prevents unnecessary SYNC_CHAINS state drops on fully synced nodes.

Applied to 3 timeout paths in dap_chain_net.c s_sync_timer_callback:
- Legacy single timeout path
- Split timeout liveness path
- Split timeout progress path
